# Snapshot: code/casts_and_memory

## Case 01

### Source: `test/tmp_fs/code.frog`

```frog
5 int ? cast ? print
```

### Run

Command:

```text
py -m frog run test/tmp_fs/code.frog
```

Output:

```text
[INFO] test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:7: Stack at compile time:
[NOTE] stack:
      0. INT()@test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:1
      1. TYPE(INT())@test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:3
[WARN] test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:9: redundant cast INT() to INT()
[INFO] test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:14: Stack at compile time:
[NOTE] stack:
      0. INT()@test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:9
[INFO] test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:7: Stack at runtime:
[NOTE] stack:
      0. INT():5@test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:1
      1. TYPE(INT()):INT()@test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:3
[WARN] test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:9: redundant cast INT() to INT()
[INFO] test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:14: Stack at runtime:
[NOTE] stack:
      0. INT():5@test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:9
[PRINT] INT():5@test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:9
```

### Build

Command:

```text
py -m frog -l WARN build -r test/tmp_fs/code.frog
```

Output:

```text
[WARN] test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:9: redundant cast INT() to INT()
[WARN] test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:9: redundant cast INT() to INT()
[CMD] gcc test/tmp_fs/code.c -o test/tmp_fs/code.exe
[CMD] test/tmp_fs/code.exe
[STDOUT]:
5

```

